  "body": "Hi, sometimes we want statical classes and toggled classes, e.g.\n\n``` js\n(this.state.hidden) ? 'my-component hidden' : 'my-component'\n// or\nthis.props.componentClass + (this.state.hidden) ? ' hidden' : ''\n```\n\nwith `classSet`, this looks like\n\n``` js\nclassSet({ 'my-component': true, hidden: this.state.hidden })\n// or\nthis.props.componentClass + ' ' + classSet({ hidden: this.state.hidden })\n// tbh, with ECMA 2015, this is\nclassSet({ [this.props.componentClass]: true, hidden: this.state.hidden })\n```\n\nthis gets ugly fast. let’s allow\n\n``` js\nclassSet('my-component', {hidden: this.state.hidden })\n// or\nclassSet(this.props.componentClass, { hidden: this.state.hidden })\n```\n\nidk how flexible this needs to be. the most simple to implement version would be\n\n``` js\nclassSet(<object-of-optionals>, ...<0-∞ static strings>)\n// e.g.\nclassSet({foo: bar}, 'baz', barf)\nclassSet({foo: bar})\n```\n\nthe most flexible would be\n\n``` js\nclassSet(...<0-∞ static strings and objects of optionals>)\n// e.g.\nclassSet(barf, {foo: bar}, 'baz', {a: b})\n```\n",
